data.title: Southeast Missouri State University Athletics
data.meta_description: Serena WilliamsSprints/Jumps  - 2023 Outdoor: Competed in eight meets…Posted 14 top-five finishes including eight top-three finishes…Started the season placing second
data.text:
2023 Outdoor: Competed in eight meets…Posted 14 top-five finishes including eight top-three finishes…Started the season placing second in the long jump, jumping for a distance of 18’ 10.75” (5.76m) and finished in fifth place during the 100-meter with a time of 12.13 at the 2023 South Alabama Invitational…Tailed a sixth place finish in the 4x100 at the 2023 Mississippi State Bulldog Relays with a time of 46.61…Finished with two third place performances at the Joey Haines Invite, in the 4x100 finishing in 46.99 and in the high jump 5’ 2.5” (1.59m)...Recorded a new personal best in the 200-meter with a run of 24.65 (17th) during the Joe Walker Invitational…Took the top spot on the podium in the 4x100 at the Cougar Classic with a time of 46.04 and placed third in the triple jump getting to the distance of 38’ 8.75” (11.80m)...Placed fourth twice at the Georgia Tech Invitational, in the 4x100 with a run of 46.23 and in the triple jump clearing the height of 39’ 3.25” (11.97m)...Placed third in the high jump 5’ 0.5” (1.54m) and third in the long jump with a jump of 18’ 5.75” (5.63m) at the Memphis Tiger Invitational. At the 2023 Outdoor OVC Championships placed second in the 4x100 crossing the line at 45.47, placed ninth in the high jump 5’ 1” (1.55m), finished in eight in the long jump getting to the distance of 18’ 7.25” (5.67m), and took home the silver medal with a jump of 38’ 10.5” (11.85m) in the triple jump.

2023 Indoor: Competed in eight meets…Posted 13 top-five finishes including six top-three finishes…Named OVC female field athlete of the week once…To begin the season at the Edmonds-Wilt Invitational placed third in the triple jump with a jump of (11.65m) 38’ 2.75’’...At the 2023 Redhawks Invite set a PR of (1.65m) 5’ 5’’ in the high jump and obtained first…She would also place first in the triple jump with a jump of (11.70m) 38’ 4.75’’...At the John Gartland Invitational set a PR in the 60 meter and placed fourth with a run of 7.82…At the 2023 Indiana University Relays placed third in the triple jump with a distance of 37’3.25’ (11.36m) and fifth in long jump 17' 8" (5.38m)...Posted a fifth place finish in the triple jump, jumping 36' 5" (11.10m), at the Hoosier Hills invite… At the 2023 Redhawks Open received a second place finish in the high jump, jumping 5’ 1’’ (1.55m)... At the Indoor OVC championship competed in the triple jump where she placed third going the distance of 38’ 11.5’’ (11.87m) and an eighth place finish in the high jump going 5’ 1’’ (1.55m).

2022 Outdoor: Competed in eight meets…Notched 11 top five finishes…Opened the season with two fourth- place runs clocking 12.13 in the 100m and 25.29 in the 200m at the Rhodes College Invitational…Notched a 47.05 (2nd) run at the Joey Haines Invite…At the Memphis Tiger Invitational, she jumped 40’ 4.75” (12.31m) in the triple jump for a second-place finish, ran the 4x100 in 47.09 for a first place showing and placed third in the 100m (12.17)…She placed second, third, and fourth, in the long jump, triple jump and high jump...Recorded a PR jump of 18’ 11.75” (5.78m), 39’ 6” (12.04m) and another PR jump of 5’ 5” (1.65m)...Also placed third in the 4x100 (46.33 ) and 10th in the 100m (12.25 ) at the Ohio Valley Conference Outdoor Championships.

2022 Indoor: Partcipated in seven meets…Posted a total of 11 top five finishes…Began the year with a 17’ 6” (5.33m) long jump to take third, a high jump of 4’ 11.75” (1.52m) to place fourth and a PR in the 55m hurdles with a time of 9.94 to get fifth at the Redhawks Invitational…Took the first place medal at the John Gartland Invitational in the triple jump, jumping 39’ 1.75” (11.93m)...At the Indiana Relays she posted a PR in the pentathlon with 2,974 points (8th)...Placed second and fourth in the triple jump and the 200m, jumping 39’ 5.25” (12.02m) and running 26.06 in the 200m at the Hoosier Hills meet…At the Redhawks Open, she jumped 39’ 3” (11.96m) (2nd) in the triple jump, ran the 55m in 7.46 (3rd) and ran her second 55m in 7.38 (2nd)...Took 11th place in the pentathlon with 2,677 points while setting a PR in the 60m hurdles (9.63 ) and a PR in shot put (25’ 10”, 7.87m)...She also placed fourth and fifth in the triple jump and high jump, jumping 38’ 5.5” (11.72m) and 18’ 1.75” (5.53m).

2021 Indoor: Competed in three indoor meets…Had seven top-four finishes and six first place finishes…Won the 55 meters (7.39), long jump (17-9, 5.41m) and triple jump (38-2.25, 11.64m) at the Redhawks Invite (2/5)…Also was fourth in the 200 meters in 27.76…Achieved a personal best 60 meters time (7.91, 11th) at the Samford Bulldog Open (2/13)…Scored a personal best in the 55 meters (7.37) at the Redhawks Open (2/20) for first…Also was first in the triple jump (38-9, 11.81m) and high jump (5-3, 1.60m).

2021 Outdoor: Competed in nine outdoor meets…Had 14 top-five finishes…Placed third in the triple jump (38-5.5, 11.72m) at the USA Invitational (3/12)… Recorded a personal best at the in the 100 meter hurdles (15.25, 11th) at the Ole Miss Classic (3/26-27)…Notched a PR in the triple jump (40-9.5, 12.43m) for second at the 2021 Joey Haines Invite (4/2-3)…Also was fifth in the high jump (5-3, 1.60m) and sixth in the 100 meters (12.05)…Took eighth in the heptathlon with 4,179 points at the Tennessee Relays (4/8-10)…Also was third in the 4x100 meter relay in 48.03…Recorded a personal best in the high jump with a mark of 5-4.25 (1.63m) for fifth at the Vanderbilt Black and Gold Invitational (4/16-17)…Also won the triple jump with 39-3.25 (11.97m)…Placed sixth with a personal best heptathlon score of 4,373 at the 2021 OVC Championship (5/13-15)…Was first in the heptathlon 200 meters (24.75), second in the long jump (18-4.25, 5.59m) and fourth in the 100 meter hurdles (15.35)…Earned Bronze in the triple jump with a mark of 39-5.75 (12.03m)…Also was fourth in the 4x100 meter relay (46.30), eighth in the 100 meters after setting a PR of 11.93 in the prelims and 11th in the high jump (5-2.5, 1.59m).

Maryville: Was at Maryville University in 2019-20.
